The paper deals with massively parallel computation paradigms and algorithms for solving graph problems such as maximal independent set and maximal matching on sparse graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on parallel and distributed computation, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories. The use of arboricity as a parameter also suggests a connection to cs.DM. The paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, but the use of parallel computation is a common technique in that field, hence cs.LG is a possible category as well.
